Argentina Wages Rose 2.10% in August From Month Ago

-- B y   F e r n a n d o   S i m o n
-- 
2011-10-03T19:10:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/argentina-wages-rose-2-10-in-august-from-month-ago-table-.html
Following is a summary of the Aug.
wage index from the Argentina National Statistics and Census 
Institute in  Buenos Aires :  NOTE: 4th quarter 2001 = 100.  Data is collected monthly by surveying
private companies and a network of correspondants in the public sector;
unregistered private sector wages are estimated.  Weights for the 
overall index are private registered (50.2%), private unregistered (19.9%),
and public sector (29.9%).  SOURCE: Instituto Nacional de Estadistica y Censos  To contact the reporter on this story:
